column35: Executive Order Targets Competition Policy Across Industries

The order instructs the FTC and DOJ to revisit merger review standards and directs sector-specific regulators to consider competitive effects in their approval processes. While executive orders cannot directly alter statutory antitrust standards, they shape agency priorities and resource allocation. Legal analysts note that the order's breadth is unusual and may signal a sustained shift in the regulatory environment for large-scale transactions across all affected sectors.
